Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the development of a new family of algorithms for matrix multiplication, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper also discusses the impact of memory bandwidth on the performance of matrix multiplication algorithms, which is related to hardware architecture. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): Matrix multiplication is a fundamental operation in numerical analysis, and the paper discusses the performance of different algorithms for this operation. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the optimality of current matrix multiplication algorithms and proposes a new family of algorithms, which is related to computational complexity. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the implementation and performance of different matrix multiplication algorithms on custom-built architectures, which is related to software engineering.
